 and Inhibitory (currents) during appetitive training B) i) The relative
 timing of firings of the pre and post synaptic neurons induce changes in
 the synaptic 'tag' variable according to the dopamine modulated STDP learning
 rule.
 ii) The synaptic tag decays to zero (top), but if extracellular dopamine
 are present during the critical time window (middle) the maximal synaptic
 conductance w is modified (iii) The synaptic weight, here written as w
 depresses as there have been pre-post spike pairs and dopamine is present
 in the system
