\begin_layout Plain Layout
A) We have trained a single odour first with an appetitive reinforcement
 and afterwards with aversive reinforcement.
 The odour first occupied a position in the approach area of the MBON valence
 space.
 After aversive training the odour moved into the area of the retreat valence
 space B) We have now trained an odour with an aversive reinforcement first
 and afterwards with appetitive reinforcement.
 The odour remained in the retreat area of the valence space after the two
 types of training.
 
\end_layout

